# Architecture Conventions

## Where logic lives

- Business logic (audio mixing, session, Supabase queries, R2 URLs) belongs in `src/lib/` — never in page or component files
- Scene metadata and texture catalog live in `src/data/textures.ts` and Supabase — not hardcoded in components
- API routes go in `src/app/api/` — keep them thin; delegate to `src/lib/`

## Component organization

- Components are feature-organized: `map/`, `scene-player/`, `audio-mixer/`, `scene-search/`, `admin/`
- Use Server Components by default; add `"use client"` only for map, audio, interactivity

## Dependencies

- Do not add new dependencies without checking bundle size impact, especially in the map/audio paths
- Prefer native browser APIs (Web Audio API) over third-party audio libs

## Session

- No user login for public features — session token in `localStorage` persists mix levels per scene
- Use `src/lib/session.ts` for all token and storage access
